y.builtins import` sites and confirm they all resolve.\n46\t5. All tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n47\t\n48\t## Technical Approach\n49\t\n50\t### Delete old test file\n51\t\n52\t```bash\n53\tgit rm tests/test_builtins.py\n54\t```\n55\t\n56\t### Audit `__init__.py`\n57\t\n58\tEnsure it only contains:\n59\t- Imports from `_registry` (`BUILTINS`, `BuiltInFunc`, `builtin`)\n60\t- Submodule imports to trigger registration\n61\t- `__all__` re-exports\n62\t- No function bodies\n63\t\n64\t### Audit `_shared.py`\n65\t\n66\tVerify each helper in `_shared.py` is imported by 2+ submodules. If any helper is used by only one, move it into that submodule.\n67\t\n68\t### Import site verification\n69\t\n70\t```bash\n71\tgrep -rn \"from darkfactory.builtins import\" src/ tests/ workflows/\n72\tgrep -rn \"from darkfactory import builtins\" src/ tests/ workflows/\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\tConfirm all import sites resolve without error.\n76\t\n77\t## Acceptance Criteria\n78\t\n79\t- [ ] AC-1: `tests/test_builtins.py` is deleted.\n80\t- [ ] AC-2: `builtins/__init__.py` contains only imports and re-exports — no builtin implementations.\n81\t- [ ] AC-3: Every helper in `_shared.py` is used by 2+ builtins.\n82\t- [ ] AC-4: All `from darkfactory.builtins import X` sites in the codebase resolve.\n83\t- [ ] AC-5: All tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n84\t- [ ] AC-6: No dead code remains from the old monolith.\n85\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c399ad7-96c2-4a07-b000-029b2ffce508","uuid":"a118e469-6ce6-49e1-96f1-5033e7afd688","timestamp":